WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:03.002
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:28.061 --> 00:31.063
>> Gumball: You know what?
I don't think I'm gonna wear
this anymore.

00:31.065 --> 00:33.399
>> Darwin: Why?
I thought it brought you good
luck.

00:33.401 --> 00:37.636
>> Gumball: Yeah, it does, but
nothing's fun anymore.
See? Watch this.

00:40.673 --> 00:44.143
>> All: Whoa!
>> Gumball: Ta-da.
Whoop-de-boring-do.

00:44.145 --> 00:47.513
>> Darwin: What are you talking
about?!
That was fan-flapping-tastic!

00:47.515 --> 00:51.750
>> Gumball: Yeah, a week ago,
maybe, but now it's just lame.
I think I'm gonna throw it out.

00:51.752 --> 00:54.953
>> Dad: don't throw it out!!
I could really use some luck
right now.

00:54.955 --> 00:58.490
I've been trying to get on
"win or don't win" for five
months, but they're not

00:58.492 --> 01:02.161
returning my calls.
>> Anais: You're never gonna get
on that show, hat or no hat.

01:02.163 --> 01:04.830
>> Dad: [ Gasps ]
There's a show called
"hat or no hat"?

01:04.832 --> 01:10.269
>> Gumball: Look, you want it?
You have it.
[ Telephone rings ]

01:10.271 --> 01:14.506
>> Dad: Hello?
Would i?!
[ Gasps ] Tomorrow?!

01:14.508 --> 01:18.977
Oh, thank you,
"win or don't win"!
Wow! This hat is amazing!

01:18.979 --> 01:23.348
>> Mom: Okay, guys, as
impressive as all this is,
let's not get carried away.

01:23.350 --> 01:27.319
There's no way a tinfoil hat is
responsible for --
Richard! What are you --

01:27.321 --> 01:30.522
[ cellphone vibrates ]
[ Beep ]
Hello?

01:30.524 --> 01:35.794
Interview? Tomorrow?
For a promotion and a pay rise?!
[ Gong! ]

01:35.796 --> 01:40.999
>> Darwin: What was that?
>> Anais: That was the sound of
doom for the wattersons.

01:41.001 --> 01:42.968
[ Whistle blows ]

01:45.772 --> 01:48.340
[ Whistle blows ]
>> Darwin: Do you ever miss your
helmet?

01:48.342 --> 01:51.777
>> Gumball: No. Why?
>> Darwin: Well, everyone seems
to be using it for really cool

01:51.779 --> 01:56.115
stuff, like dad with the TV show
or mom with her job.
All you ever did was lame party

01:56.117 --> 01:58.750
tricks.
>> Gumball: It doesn't matter,
Darwin.

01:58.752 --> 02:03.021
I'm happy to see the back of it.
Succeeding at everything really
took the joy out of life.

02:03.023 --> 02:06.859
Besides...
Sometimes in life, you make your
own luck!

02:06.861 --> 02:12.264
[ Grunts ]
[ Muffled ] It's so good to fail
again.

02:12.266 --> 02:17.336
You see, you take a pinch of
success, a dash of failure, you
mix it together, and that's what

02:17.338 --> 02:21.640
makes life int--
[ Boom! ]
See? That wasn't so bad.

02:21.642 --> 02:25.544
>> Darwin: You just blew up the
ant farm.
[ Ants grumbling ]

02:25.546 --> 02:29.181
>> Gumball: Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!
It's okay!
Aah!

02:29.183 --> 02:34.620
Life is great, Darwin!
Ah! Ow! Ow! Ow!
>> Darwin: So, you're saying

02:34.622 --> 02:38.790
you're happy when you fail?
>> Gumball: Absolutely.
It's the struggle that makes a

02:38.792 --> 02:45.731
victory sweet.
Besides, i still got it.
>> Darwin: Aaaah!

02:45.733 --> 02:49.868
>> Butter side down, just like
poor uncle Eddie.
>> What do you know --

02:49.870 --> 02:54.106
my lunch is on the floor.
Hey, who's the funny guy who did
that?

02:54.108 --> 02:57.309
[ Sloop! ]
[ Slump! ]
>> Gumball: [ Echoing ] And you

02:57.311 --> 03:00.279
know what the best thing about
failure is, Darwin?
>> Darwin: [ Muffled ] No.

03:00.281 --> 03:03.215
[ Ptoo! ]
>> Gumball: Is that it builds
your sense of humor.

03:03.217 --> 03:10.355
[ Laughs ]
[ Sobs ]
Oh, who am i kidding?

03:10.357 --> 03:16.895
I'm nothing without my helmet!
I want it back!
[ Deep voice ] I need it!

03:16.897 --> 03:22.434
>> Dad: But i need it<i> more,</i>
'cause i need to win the show!
>> Mom: Well,<i> i</i> need it to get

03:22.436 --> 03:26.505
the promotion, which is more
important than a game show.
>> Dad: But if i win the show,

03:26.507 --> 03:30.475
I'll get a speedboat!
Think about how great it would
be for<i> me!</i>

03:30.477 --> 03:33.879
>> Mom: Richard, you'll never
use it.
>> Dad: Nicole, if i win a

03:33.881 --> 03:38.450
speedboat, I'm<i> gonna</i> use it.
>> Mom: You have to understand,
I'm doing this for the greater

03:38.452 --> 03:41.753
good.
Winning the speedboat will be
good for<i> you</i> but not for the

03:41.755 --> 03:48.026
rest of the family.
>> Dad: Ohh...You're right.
I'm sorry, Nicole.

03:48.028 --> 03:51.597
I-i don't know what came over
me.
>> Mom: It's okay.

03:51.599 --> 03:57.002
Just, where did you hide the
helmet?
>> Dad: It's in this bag.

03:57.004 --> 03:59.938
Oh...
[ Groans ]
No, wait!

03:59.940 --> 04:05.410
Actually, it's in -- it's in
this one.
I was gonna trick you.

04:05.412 --> 04:11.016
I'm sorry.
I guess that helmet's got more
power over me than i thought.

04:11.018 --> 04:16.655
>> Mom: Thanks for being honest,
honey.
>> That was an astonishing

04:16.657 --> 04:20.192
interview.
There's...Just one thing.
[ Laughing ] You<i> are</i> aware that

04:20.194 --> 04:24.096
if you get the job, you won't be
able to wear that papier-mâché
helmet, right?

04:24.098 --> 04:27.599
>> Mom: [ Laughs ]
Of course.
But for the record, it's not

04:27.601 --> 04:30.302
papier-mâché.
It's tinfoil.
>> Mm, no.

04:30.304 --> 04:35.073
I'm pretty sure it's
papier-mâché painted gray.
>> Mom: What?

04:35.075 --> 04:41.880
Can i switch your TV on?
>> Uh...Sure?
>><i> And he's won the speedboat!</i>

04:41.882 --> 04:45.751
>> Dad:<i> Yay!</i>
[<i> Dance music plays</i> ]

04:54.894 --> 04:59.831
>> Mom: [ Panting ]
This isn't going to affect my
chances, is it?

04:59.833 --> 05:04.236
>> Um, what do<i> you</i> think?
>> Mom: [ Grunts ]
>> Dad: It's mine!

05:04.238 --> 05:08.240
>> Gumball: No, mine!
Give it back! Give it back!
>> Dad: It's mine!

05:08.242 --> 05:11.376
>> Mom: I lost my job for it!
>> Dad: It's mine!
[ Both grunt ]

05:11.378 --> 05:14.146
>> Gumball: I need it!
>> Dad: But I'm on "hat or no
hat" tomorrow!

05:14.148 --> 05:16.415
>> Mom: Give...
>> Dad: It...
>> Gumball: Back!

05:16.417 --> 05:21.453
>> Anais: Stop it!
Look at what you've become!
This stupid hat is driving you

05:21.455 --> 05:24.022
crazy!
>> Gumball: Actually, it's a
helmet.

05:24.024 --> 05:27.626
>> Anais: It's not a helmet or a
hat!
It's a piece of tinfoil!

05:27.628 --> 05:30.796
And it's tearing this family
apart!
Look at you!

05:30.798 --> 05:35.300
You're behaving like animals!
>> Mom: [ Sighs ]
Anais is right.

05:35.302 --> 05:38.503
That helmet has such a grip on
us.
>> Dad: It's like its magic is

05:38.505 --> 05:41.440
taking control of the person who
wears it.
>> Gumball: Ha!

05:41.442 --> 05:44.643
Well, since none of you guys
want it, i guess i can have it
back.

05:44.645 --> 05:48.347
>> Anais: No!
Me and Darwin have been talking,
and we've decided it has to be

05:48.349 --> 05:50.849
destroyed.
>> Gumball: What?!
You can't destroy it!

05:50.851 --> 05:53.985
I'm nothing without it!
>> Mom: I'm sorry, honey, but
anais is right.

05:53.987 --> 05:56.621
>> Gumball: Can -- can i have
one more go?
>> Anais: No!

05:56.623 --> 05:59.624
>> Gumball: don't touch it!!
>> Dad: Hey!
>> Gumball: No! No! No!

05:59.626 --> 06:01.993
It's mine!
Aah! Aah!
No! It's my helmet!

06:01.995 --> 06:05.564
>> Darwin: Dude, chill out.
It's just a bucket with some
tinfoil on it.

06:05.566 --> 06:10.635
>> Gumball: Aaah! Give it back!
It's my helmet!
Aaaaaaaaaaaaaah!

06:14.574 --> 06:17.976
>> Darwin: Why can't we just put
it in the bin?
>> Anais: Because they'll just

06:17.978 --> 06:22.447
pull it out again.
We have to take it to the bin of
all bins -- the dump.

06:25.818 --> 06:28.320
>> Darwin: Can't we just rip it
up?
>> Anais: Have you ever tried

06:28.322 --> 06:30.956
ripping up tinfoil?
Sounds horrible.
>> Darwin: What are we gonna do

06:30.958 --> 06:34.993
with it, then?
>> Anais: Throw it in the
garbage crusher.

06:34.995 --> 06:41.800
>> Gumball: [ Breathing
heavily ]
[ Breathing continues ]

06:41.802 --> 06:45.203
>> Darwin: Can you hear that?
>> Anais: What?
>> Darwin: That noise.

06:45.205 --> 06:48.774
Sounds like a cat trying to say
"snake."
>> Gumball: [ Echoing ] Snake.

06:48.776 --> 06:51.676
>> Anais: It's probably just the
wind.
>> Darwin: Mm. Maybe.

06:51.678 --> 06:55.380
I don't know what the big deal
with this lucky helmet is,
anyway.

06:55.382 --> 07:00.886
Looks pretty normal to me.
Oh, look -- a gold ring!
Oh, look -- a pearly necklace!

07:00.888 --> 07:05.390
Wow!
A diamond-encrusted chain!
And it spells "Darwin"!

07:05.392 --> 07:09.528
>> Anais: [ Panting ]
Come on.
We're nearly there.

07:09.530 --> 07:15.967
>> Darwin: [ Panting ]
I-i can't do it, anais.
It's -- it's too heavy.

07:15.969 --> 07:18.837
>> Anais: Well, give me the
helmet.
I'll deal with it.

07:18.839 --> 07:23.041
>> Darwin: No!
It's a man's job.
You're -- you're just a little

07:23.043 --> 07:27.946
girl.
The helmet is<i> my</i> burden to
carry.

07:27.948 --> 07:33.351
You can carry<i> me,</i> though!
>> Anais: [ Growls ]
[ Panting loudly ]

07:44.497 --> 07:47.833
[ Panting continues ]
There.
I've done my part.

07:47.835 --> 07:51.703
Now you do<i> yours.</i>
Throw the stupid thing in the
crusher.

07:51.705 --> 07:58.777
>> Darwin: Okay!
Well, good riddance!
>> Anais: Darwin, look out!

07:58.779 --> 08:02.013
>> Gumball: [ Raspy voice ] Give
me my helmet!
The helmet's mine! Give it back!

08:02.015 --> 08:04.749
Give it! Give it!
>> Darwin: Dude, what's wrong
with your voice?

08:04.751 --> 08:07.018
>> Gumball: I just really need
to cough.
[ Coughs ]

08:07.020 --> 08:09.020
[ Normal voice ] Better.
Aha!
>> Darwin: No!

08:09.022 --> 08:12.290
>> Gumball: [ Laughs evilly ]
>> Anais: Give it up, gumball!
There's two of us!

08:12.292 --> 08:16.094
You'll never win!
>> Gumball: Oh, yeah?
[ Laughs evilly ]

08:16.096 --> 08:21.166
I can already feel its power!
>> Anais: Well, not for long!
Come on, Darwin.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.468
>> Gumball: [ Laughing evilly ]

08:25.371 --> 08:30.675
You'll never hit me!
I'm the luckiest man alive!
>> Anais: It's not luck!

08:30.677 --> 08:33.512
It's just we can't throw very
well!
>> Gumball: Then let me make it

08:33.514 --> 08:38.683
easy for you.
>> Darwin: Come on, anais!
There's no way you can miss from

08:38.685 --> 08:44.122
there!
>> Anais: [ Exhales deeply ]
[ Grunts ]

08:44.124 --> 08:48.760
Huh.
>> Gumball: [ Laughs evilly ]
Nice try, but now it's<i> my</i> turn.

08:48.762 --> 08:51.963
Oh, look -- a tennis-ball
machine.
>> Anais: [ Scoffs ]

08:51.965 --> 08:55.700
Good luck finding a power supply
for that.
>> Gumball: Oh, look -- a

08:55.702 --> 08:59.137
generator.
>> Anais: Okay, maybe the hat<i> is</i>
magic after all.

08:59.139 --> 09:02.140
Run!!
>> Gumball: [ Laughing evilly ]

09:05.478 --> 09:09.581
>> Anais: He's got us cornered!
What are we gonna do?!
>> Darwin: Pass me that stale

09:09.583 --> 09:12.517
baguette.
>> Anais: Why?
>> Darwin: don't you worry about

09:12.519 --> 09:14.653
it.
Just tell mom and dad i love
them.

09:14.655 --> 09:19.758
>> Anais: What? Darwin, no!
>> Darwin: [ Yells in slow
motion ]

09:22.161 --> 09:30.268
>> Anais: [ Slow motion ] No!
>> Gumball: [ Laughs evilly ]
No! My power!

09:30.270 --> 09:35.006
>> Anais: Come on, Darwin!
He lost the helmet!
>> Darwin: Oh, cool.

09:37.043 --> 09:42.280
>> Gumball: No! No! No, no!
No!!
>> Anais: Gumball!!

09:42.282 --> 09:44.249
[ Gasps ]

09:46.352 --> 09:51.856
>> Gumball: [ Straining ]
Almost...Got...It.
>> Anais: What the --

09:51.858 --> 09:56.561
what is wrong with you?!
>> Gumball: My helmet...
I can almost reach it.

09:56.563 --> 10:01.499
>> Anais: Give me your hand!
>> Gumball: No!
I need the power!

10:01.501 --> 10:04.703
[ Straining ]
[ Gasps ]
>> Darwin: For goodness' sake,

10:04.705 --> 10:08.306
man!
It's only a piece of tinfoil!
>> Gumball: But think of all the

10:08.308 --> 10:13.645
stuff we could do with it.
[ Straining ]
Yes! Ha ha!

10:13.647 --> 10:18.783
Okay, you can pull me up now.
>> Anais: Listen, gumball, the
helmet is powerful, but it's

10:18.785 --> 10:22.854
also evil.
>> Darwin: Look at what it's
done to you and mom and dad!

10:22.856 --> 10:27.292
>> Gumball: But -- but without
it, I'm nothing!
>> Anais: Gumball,<i> we're</i> nothing

10:27.294 --> 10:30.629
without<i> you.</i>
So, give me your other hand.

10:36.969 --> 10:42.140
[ All straining ]
>> Darwin: Whoo.

10:47.546 --> 10:52.584
[ All groan ]
[ All grunting ]

10:57.256 --> 11:00.792
Yay!
[ Laughter ]

11:05.331 --> 11:10.435
>> Mom: Richard, are you sure
this is a good idea?
>> Dad: Of course, honey.

11:10.437 --> 11:16.041
I said I'd use it, didn't i?
>> Gumball: Uh, how far away
is the sea?

11:16.043 --> 11:18.276
>> Dad: Oh, about 100 miles.

11:26.520 --> 11:31.790
>><i> And welcome to the</i>
<i>welterweight title.</i>
>> Anais: [ Sniffs ]

11:31.792 --> 11:35.226
Huh?
You okay?
>> Gumball: Yep.

11:35.228 --> 11:40.398
School was awesome today!
I was hanging out with Tina.
She taught me how to donate to

11:40.400 --> 11:42.967
charity.
Who is this for, again?
>> Me.

11:42.969 --> 11:46.871
>> Gumball: Then she helped tear
through my homework.
>> [ Laughs ]

11:46.873 --> 11:52.477
>> Gumball: And finally, we had
lunch together.
What should i try first?

11:52.479 --> 11:57.782
[ Grunts ]
Mmm. Lasagna.
It was great!

11:57.784 --> 12:00.552
What?
>> Anais: I think you're being
bullied.

12:00.554 --> 12:04.155
>> Gumball: Nah.
We're just having fun.
>> Anais: Mmmm...Nope.

12:04.157 --> 12:07.258
You're definitely getting
bullied.
>> Gumball: [ Gasps ]

12:07.260 --> 12:10.962
What am i gonna do?!
>> Anais: don't worry, bro.
I'll take care of this for you.

12:10.964 --> 12:15.633
[ Beep, ringing ]
Hey, Tina, you've been picking
on my brother, and i think it's

12:15.635 --> 12:19.571
time you guys talked about this
face-to-face.
>> [ Roars ]

12:19.573 --> 12:22.607
>> Anais: Tomorrow?
>> [ Roars ]
>> Anais: 4:00 P.M.?

12:22.609 --> 12:25.577
>> [ Roars ]
>> Anais: Behind the school?!
No, wait!

12:25.579 --> 12:28.146
That's not what i meant!
[ Dial tone ]
Oopsie.

12:28.148 --> 12:30.915
[ Beep ]
>> Gumball: Well?
>> Anais: Looks like your

12:30.917 --> 12:35.754
face-to-face turned into more of
a...Face-to-fist.
>> Gumball: What the --

12:35.756 --> 12:38.523
what?!
>> Anais: I think she wants to
have a fight with you.

12:38.525 --> 12:42.026
[<i> Bell dings</i> ]
>><i> He's out cold!</i>
>> Dad: Come on, son.

12:42.028 --> 12:48.299
It's time i showed you how to
deal with bullies.
There comes a point in every

12:48.301 --> 12:53.872
man's life where he has to stand
up for himself.
But that's okay, 'cause daddy's

12:53.874 --> 12:59.077
here to teach you an old family
technique that got me out of
trouble many times.

12:59.079 --> 13:03.715
>> Gumball: Oooh.
A secret fighting technique?
>> Dad: Yes.

13:03.717 --> 13:09.154
It's called...
The bunny hop.
But remember, you must never use

13:09.156 --> 13:13.525
it in anger.
>> Gumball: I promise, father.
>> Dad: All right.

13:13.527 --> 13:16.528
You be the bully.
>> Gumball: Okay.
>> Dad: Come on. don't be shy.

13:16.530 --> 13:21.032
Try to take my lunch money.
>> Gumball: [ Meows ]
>> Dad: Aah! don't hurt me!

13:21.034 --> 13:23.568
Not the face!
Here's my lunch money -- and my
lunch!

13:23.570 --> 13:28.139
Please, take it!
Please, please, please!
That was step one.

13:28.141 --> 13:34.078
And here comes the bunny hop.
Hah.
Blblblblblblblblblblblblbl!

13:37.116 --> 13:40.385
>> Gumball: Well, that wasn't
much help.
>> Anais: You're right.

13:40.387 --> 13:47.025
I think you need help from a
<i>real</i> adult.
>> So, school counselor.

13:47.027 --> 13:52.297
Pretty scary title, huh?
But don't you worry your tiny,
little heads about it.

13:52.299 --> 14:00.038
Think of me as a friend, a
compadre, a fellow pilgrim on a
mad journey we call...

14:00.040 --> 14:03.775
Life.
So, tell me, what's shakin'?
>> Gumball: Oh, I'm fine.

14:03.777 --> 14:06.945
>> Anais: No, he's not!
He's being bullied!
>> Oh.

14:06.947 --> 14:12.951
The big "b," huh?
You know, more often than not,
conversation beats

14:12.953 --> 14:16.254
confrontation.
Hands down.

14:16.256 --> 14:25.430
Let's meditate on this.
>> Both: Ohmmmmmmm.
Ohmmmmmmmmmmm.

14:25.432 --> 14:28.533
>> So, tell me, who's bullying
you?
>> Both: Tina Rex.

14:28.535 --> 14:31.269
>> [ Gasps ]
Tina Rex?!

14:34.673 --> 14:38.943
don't tell her you saw me!
>> Anais: Well, that wasn't much
help.

14:38.945 --> 14:42.447
>> No way!
Gumball's gonna fight Tina?
>> She's gonna mash him!

14:42.449 --> 14:46.484
>> He's toast!
>> She's gonna skin him alive!
>> This will be the greatest

14:46.486 --> 14:49.888
fight ever!
>> Gumball: This is getting out
of hand.

14:49.890 --> 14:52.423
>> Anais: don't worry.
I'll fix this.
Come on!

14:52.425 --> 14:57.128
What is wrong with you guys?
How many of you have been
bullied by Tina?

14:57.130 --> 14:59.530
>> Maybe.
>> I guess.
>> I have.

14:59.532 --> 15:05.403
>> Anais: don't you realize if
we all join forces, we can stand
up to Tina once and for all?

15:05.405 --> 15:10.341
[ Indistinct talking ]
And no student will ever be
bullied again!

15:10.343 --> 15:13.244
>> All: Yeah!
>> Anais: We can also stop
global warming!

15:13.246 --> 15:16.047
>> All: Yeah!
>> Anais: And bring peace to the
world!

15:16.049 --> 15:19.851
>> All: Yeah!
>> Anais: And build schools for
the dolphins in the rainforests

15:19.853 --> 15:23.988
so they can cure baldness!
>> All: Yeah!
>> Gumball: Uh, anais?

15:23.990 --> 15:27.892
>> Anais: Sorry, gumball!
The power's gone to my head!
See you on capitol hill!

15:27.894 --> 15:31.863
>> Good luck with the fight,
man!
[ Laughs ]

15:31.865 --> 15:34.332
>> Darwin: There you are.
>> Gumball: [ Shrieks ]
Darwin!

15:34.334 --> 15:37.535
You're supposed to be here when
your best friend's about to get
mangled by --

15:37.537 --> 15:41.673
>> Darwin: Shhhhhhhhhhhh!
Just follow me!

15:46.578 --> 15:51.316
Behold my super bully protection
suit of power!

15:54.853 --> 15:57.055
>> Gumball: Whoa!

15:59.992 --> 16:07.098
I love it!
>> Darwin: [ Imitates whirring ]
Pshooo!

16:07.100 --> 16:10.001
>> Gumball: [ Breathing
heavily ]
>> Darwin: Looking good.

16:10.003 --> 16:15.740
Now, check<i> this</i> out.
It's got bouncy bubble wrap
pants, and it has an mp3 player

16:15.742 --> 16:19.077
as standard.
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

16:23.382 --> 16:29.087
And that's not all.
This string here operates the
super counterattack device.

16:29.089 --> 16:33.091
No, wait!
You've only got one shot, so you
must wait for the right moment.

16:33.093 --> 16:38.029
>> Gumball: Okay.
>> Darwin: And last but not
